@RealChrnblChckn Every system will eventually be corrupted by the powerful economic interests that stand to directly benefit from capturing the regulatory authorities for their respective industries.

@RealChrnblChckn From the perspective of someone living the the US, arguing about "Republic" vs. "Democracy" for politics is as shallow as "Capitalism" vs. "Socialism" for economics.

The answer here will be a mixture of both. The real questions will be about what mixture is appropriate.

@RealChrnblChckn "Many forms of Government have been tried, and will be tried in this world of sin and woe. No one pretends that democracy is perfect. Indeed it has been said that democracy is the worst form of Government except for all those other forms that have been tried from time to time.‚Ä¶"

@RealChrnblChckn I'm talking about changing the voting system from first-past-the-post to something like Ranked Choice, STAR, or Approval Voting. 

My tweet had nothing to do with abolishing the Electoral College. (Tho that would help establishment more of a democratic process in this country.)

How many times do we need to have one of these terrible "vote for this asshole to prevent that asshole from winning" elections before there's a popular nationwide movement to change the voting system?

Many alternatives exist. Almost all of them are better than what we're using.
